<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Phrases 1 and 2 are structurally identical text — same harmony, varied texture.
  P1: block half-note LH, static RH open 5th. P2: RH arpeggio ascending in m5, dotted passing in m6.
- vii° (G#°): G#2-B2-D3 in LH — diminished triad as a half-step leading tone cluster before I.
- V7 in mm. 2, 6: LH adds G#3 on top (E-B-E-G# = "333" seventh chord).
- vi (F#m): uses quartal F#-C#-F# voicing in LH (two perfect 4ths) — more open than 3rds.
- m10 climax at vi: F#2-C#3-F#3-A3 = four notes in LH (richest so far) with E2-B2-G#3 V for tension.
- mm. 15-16 climax: both I and IV get 4-note LH (A-E-A-C# and D-A-D-F#), RH reaches D5-F#5.
- Final m17: both hands settle to root position with full 3rds (I=A-C#-E) — converged closure.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Inner bass line mm. 1-4: A2→F#2→E2→A2 — step in outer bass voice between I and vi
- LH upper voice: across the V7 measures, G#3 provides leading-tone color resolving to A3 on I
- RH in m5 ascending arpeggio (A4-C#5-E5-C#5) adds forward motion vs the static m1

TEXTURE ARC:
- mm. 1-4: Light — 3-note LH, 2-note RH, half-note changes
- mm. 5-8: Medium — add RH arpeggio figure, same LH foundation
- mm. 9-12: Full — 4-note LH chord at I (A-E-A-C#), upper register RH (C#5-E5)
- mm. 13-16: Climax — all 4-note LH voicings, RH reaches F#5, both halves full
- m17: Single whole-note convergence — root pos both hands, quiet ending
-->
